line_1: But the flare of our colours, the tuck of our drums;
line_2: To mine eye or mine ear no gay cheering e'er comes,

line_1: By sounding Trumpets, Hear, and ratl'ing Drums,
line_2: When William to the open Vengeance comes:

line_1: So waves his Colours, beats his Drums;
line_2: He comes, the mighty Vill'roy comes;

line_1: As noisy as a dozen drums,
With Horns and with Trumpets, with Fiddles and Drums,
line_2: They'll strive to divert him as soon as he comes.
